cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with convolutional sparse representations, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image processing and object recognition. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses dictionary learning, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning and signal processing, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which are commonly studied in cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes new algorithms, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
